  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align=center cellpadding='3' width='85%'>
  <tr><td class='spti2'>PLAYER JOURNAL</td></tr>  <tr><td class='db'><font class='dbti'>Girdle of Mind and Body</font> - Lethina Lifegiver</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'> </td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>Here's my tale:<p>

GM Event in North Karana, Fennin Ro<br>
March 12th, 2001<p>

Lethina Lifegiver<br>
34th season, Cleric of Rodcet Nife<p>

At approximately 9:30pm EST on March 12th, 2001, Dartain the Lost emerged from the murky depths of the river in the Northern Plains of Karana. He proclaimed that he was seeking aid in completing a deed.<p>

As the crowd began to swarm around him near the stone bridge, I stepped forward and asked how I might be of assistance to him. He chose me to help him attain some research notes he was seeking. He had been unable to attain them from Ognit Eznertab; the short little gnome would have nothing to do with him. He explained that I must obtain the research notes from the gnome without arousing suspicion of my association with Dartain the Lost.<p>

It was to be a tactful quest. He mentioned the Hatch and the Wall of Living Stone in Old Paineel. Ognit Eznertab was known to adventure with Firiona Vie, but was last seen with Dagda Icefury in Everfrost Peaks. Dartain the Lost sent me on my way with instructions to meet him at Crows in Qeynos when I had the notes.<p>

Knowing that the journey would surely be dangerous, I was immediately offered help by many courageous adventurers. Khaladin, Gelenas, Kismeta, Ackamandar, and Keaerin offered their help and I warmly welcomed them to aid me in my quest.<p>

We headed swiftly toward Everfrost Peaks. We began our search for Dagda Icefury. When Khaladin shouted for her, she responded quickly stating that she could be found near Halas. We arrived at Halas to greet both Dagda and Ognit. They were apprehensive; for we were a formidable-looking group of adventurers! We quickly eased their minds with a statement of peace.<p>

Knowing that I must be cautious in dealing with Ognit, I devised a plan. I appealed to his ego by telling him that word of his great and brilliant notes was spreading across the land. I told him that I was seeking the notes of Hatch and the Wall of Living Stone. His only request to me was that I pay him so that he could re-supply his paper. I gave him 10 platinum pieces hoping that it would be satisfactory. He handed me the note. We thanked him and were on our way.<p>

Dartain the Lost warned that this journey would be dangerous. I took this into consideration for our journey back to Qeynos … “be ready for a fight,” I said.<p>

We teleported to the Western Plains of Karana to avoid getting lost in Everfrost Peaks; we had to proceed with all due haste. We entered Qeynos Hills and were promptly stopped by two dubious looking Erudites. Rennin Splots and Nanzell Yestle quickly surrounded me. At this point, the group was already preparing for battle … “I got this one … you get that one.”<p>

The two Erudites demanded that I hand over the note. They stated that it belonged to DarkTruth and demanded its surrender under threat of execution.<p>

Of course, I pled ignorance. They gave fair warning. It mattered little; it was they or I. The battle ensued. Knowing that I could not possibly survive the attacks of both Erudites, I cast Divine Aura. My group was already slashing away at the vile creatures. Nanzell died quickly thanks to the tactfulness of Ackamandar as he was invisible before the battle began. He positioned himself behind the Erudites and surprise attacked them. As the Divine Aura wore off; Rennin was viciously beating me. However, I managed to get off two Superior Heals and survive the battle.<p>

Thanks to the readiness of my group and battle hardened adventurers; we were victorious and suffered no casualties.<p>

We hastily made our way to Crows in North Qeynos where we found Dartain the Lost waiting outside. He greeted me with a “what took you so long” welcome and I gave him the notes. He awarded me with a magical coin to give to Jaylia the Faithful, standing nearby, for my reward. I gave the coin to her and she presented my reward, proclaiming:<p>

<blockquote>
<i>
Hear ye, hear ye! Recognize now that you hold a hero of great worth and valor among you! Lethina has been proven in the eyes of the gods! As within this mortal realm, the name shall be known within the eternal halls of the Realm of Heroes!
</i>
</blockquote>
<p>

I was awarded with the following item:<p>

Girdle of Mind and Body<br>
SLOT: WAIST<br>
MAGIC ITEM NO DROP<br>
AC 7<br>
STR +10 WIS + 10 INT +10 SV FIRE +10<br>
WT: 5.0<br>
RACE: ALL<br>
CLASS: ALL<p>

One final word: the courageous individuals who helped me complete this quest have my life-long thanks and I am forever indebted to them.
</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db2'><a href='view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Id=58380'>Return to Lethina's Journal</a></td></tr>
